data.title: NBA Players Who Can't Dunk
data.meta_description: Over 100 sports fans have voted on the 20+ athletes on NBA Players Who Can't Dunk. Current Top 3: Steve Nash, Isaiah Thomas, Jason Kidd
data.text:
Ranked By

685 votes

197 voters

Voting Rules

Vote up the best NBA players who can't dunk.

Who are the best NBA players who can't dunk? Being an NBA player without the necessary hops to dunk in a two-handed slam is kind of embarrassing. For some, not dunking can be a cheeky gimmick, like how point guard Ricky Rubio has never intentionally utilized his 6'9" wingspan to jam one home in an NBA game. For other players in NBA who can't dunk, it's due to genetics and basically not being tall enough, or not wanting to use those sneakers that jack up your calves enough to help increase vertical leaping ability. So, who is the best NBA player who can't dunk? Which NBA players with no hops do you love?

When it come to the best NBA players to never slam dunk, Steve Nash is up there with the best of them. In his 17-year NBA career, Nash attempted just one in-game dunk, in 2007, but he missed it. Then there's NBA All Stars like Jason Kidd and Jameer Nelson who couldn't dunk. There are even shooting guards who couldn't dunk like J.J. Redick and Beno Udrih.

Vote up the best NBA players who couldn't dunk, and help decide the best NBA player in history with no hops.

Most divisive: Pablo Prigioni

Over 100 Ranker voters have come together to rank this list of NBA Stars Who Can't Dunk

Height: 6'3"

Wingspan: 6'4"

Steve Nash, born February 7, 1974, in Johannesburg, South Africa, is a retired professional basketball player who is best known for his time in the NBA. Raised in Victoria, British Columbia, Canada, Nash's athletic prowess was evident from an early age, but it was during his tenure at Santa Clara University that he truly began to make waves. His remarkable skills saw him being selected as the 15th pick by the Phoenix Suns in the 1996 NBA draft, marking the start of a career that would span nearly two decades. Nash's journey in the NBA was nothing short of extraordinary. He played for teams such as the Phoenix Suns, Dallas Mavericks, and Los Angeles Lakers, bringing his unique style and vision to each game. His achievements include being named the NBA's Most Valuable Player (MVP) twice, in 2005 and 2006, an honor only a handful of players have ever received. Nash also managed to secure eight NBA All-Star designations and became one of the top ten players for assists in NBA history. His ability to create scoring opportunities for his teammates earned him a reputation as one of the best point guards in the league. Off the court, Nash has been equally impactful. He established the Steve Nash Foundation in 2001, aiming to assist underserved children in their health, personal development, education, and enjoyment of life. His philanthropic efforts extend to environmental sustainability, where he has been an outspoken advocate. Nash's commitment to the sport and society has transcended his playing career, making him an influential figure in both realms. His induction into the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame in 2018 is a testament to his significant contributions to the sport of basketball.

Birthplace : Johannesburg, South Africa

Team : Dallas Mavericks, Phoenix Suns, Los Angeles Lakers

Position : Point guard

Height: 5′ 9″

Wingspan: 6'2"

Isaiah Jamar Thomas (born February 7, 1989) is an American professional basketball player who last played for the Charlotte Hornets of the National Basketball Association (NBA). He most notably played with the Boston Celtics from 2015 through 2017, when he was a two-time NBA All-Star and named second-team All-NBA.

Birthplace : Tacoma, Washington

Team : Sacramento Kings

Position : Point guard

Height: 6'4"

Wingspan: 6'5"

Jason Frederick Kidd (born March 23, 1973) is an American professional basketball coach and former player who is the head coach for the Dallas Mavericks of the National Basketball Association (NBA). Regarded as one of the greatest point guards and passers of all time, Kidd was a 10-time NBA All-Star, a five-time All-NBA First Team member, and a nine-time NBA All-Defensive Team member. He won an NBA championship in 2011 as a member of the Dallas Mavericks and was a two-time gold medal winner in the Olympics with the U.S. national team in 2000 and 2008. He was inducted as a player into the Naismith Memorial Basketball Hall of Fame. In October 2021, Kidd was honored as one of the league's greatest players of all time by being named to the NBA 75th Anniversary Team.

Birthplace : San Francisco, California

Team : Dallas Mavericks, Phoenix Suns, New Jersey Nets, New York Knicks

Position : Point guard

Height: 6'0"

Wingspan: 6'1.5"

Fredderick Edmund VanVleet (born February 25, 1994) is an American professional basketball player for the Toronto Raptors of the National Basketball Association (NBA). In college, he has contributed to a resurgence of Wichita State Shockers basketball that included a final four run in the 2013 NCAA Men's Division I Basketball Tournament by the 2012-13 Shocker team as a freshman and an undefeated regular season by the 2013-14 team as a sophomore. He was named as a 2014 NCAA Men's Basketball All-American by a variety of media outlets. As a junior for the 2014-15 Shockers, he was an All-Missouri Valley Conference first team selection and received All-American honorable mention recognition from the Associated Press. He is the Wichita State career assists leader.

Birthplace : Rockford, Illinois

Team : Toronto Raptors

Position : Point Guard

Height: 6'3"

Wingspan: 6'3.25"

Jonathan Clay "JJ" Redick (born June 24, 1984) is an American former professional basketball player who is a podcaster and sports analyst for ESPN. He was selected 11th overall by the Orlando Magic in the 2006 NBA draft. He played college basketball for the Duke Blue Devils. In college, Redick was known for his good three-point and free throw shooting. He set ACC records during his career for most points and most career ACC tournament points, though his ACC career points record was subsequently broken by UNC's Tyler Hansbrough in 2009. Redick is currently the all-time leading scorer for Duke. He also set several other Duke records, including most points in a single season. Redick's jersey was retired by Duke on February 4, 2007. In addition to his basketball career, Redick is a podcaster, and hosts a basketball and entertainment podcast produced by Tommy Alter.

Birthplace : Cookeville, Tennessee

Team : Orlando Magic, Milwaukee Bucks, Los Angeles Clippers, Philadelphia 76ers, New Orleans Pelicans

Position : Shooting guard

Height: 5'10"

Wingspan: 6'0"

Jameer Lamar Nelson Sr. (born February 9, 1982) is an American former professional basketball player who serves as assistant general manager for the Delaware Blue Coats of the NBA G League. He played college basketball for the Saint Joseph's Hawks, where he was named national college player of the year in 2004. Drafted 20th overall in the 2004 NBA draft, Nelson spent the first ten years of his NBA career with the Orlando Magic. In 2009, he was named an All-Star and made an appearance in the NBA Finals with the Magic. He has also played for the Dallas Mavericks, Boston Celtics, Denver Nuggets, New Orleans Pelicans and Detroit Pistons.

Birthplace : Chester, Pennsylvania

Team : Orlando Magic, Dallas Mavericks, Boston Celtics, Denver Nuggets, New Orleans Pelicans

Position : Point guard
